      "writtenOn": "2018-06-22T01:27:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think that that results in another race: if the test exits before t.Run returns, the copier may receive the abort message before it finishes copying all of the output from the test. in this case, we would incorrectly report a timeout.\n\n(i used this approach at first and ended up with nondeterministically-failing unit tests. :-) )",
